{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566775","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566775"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18877"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18877"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.84,0,0.1,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11610"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79928"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11610","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11610"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18877"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65224"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11327"},{"type":"tags","id":"11331"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27319"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27320"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31829"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49015"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79928"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old doctor has been experiencing recurrent headaches and fatigue for the past three months. They have been taking over-the-counter analgesics and reviewing medical literature about their symptoms. Their hospital colleagues have offered informal advice during lunch breaks. The doctor is concerned about maintaining patient care responsibilities if they take time off to see a General Practitioner.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes appropriate healthcare management for this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Documenting self-prescribed treatment in personal health records","Establishing care with an independent General Practitioner","Obtaining laboratory tests through hospital facilities","Requesting formal consultation from specialist colleagues","Using evidence-based guidelines for self-management"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is \u003Cstrong\u003Eestablishing care with an independent general practitioner\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures objective assessment, appropriate documentation, and professional distance in healthcare decisions. It is a requirement of good medical practice for doctors to have their own GP, particularly when managing ongoing symptoms that could indicate serious conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocumenting self-prescribed treatment in personal health records\u003C/strong\u003E - Documentation does not legitimise self-prescribing, which remains inappropriate and potentially dangerous\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtaining laboratory tests through hospital facilities\u003C/strong\u003E - This represents misuse of hospital resources and lacks proper clinical oversight\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequesting formal consultation from specialist colleagues\u003C/strong\u003E - This bypasses primary care and may compromise professional relationships\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUsing evidence-based guidelines for self-management\u003C/strong\u003E - This lacks objective assessment and may miss important clinical findings due to cognitive bias\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHaving a regular GP ensures proper preventive care, including immunisations, and provides support for mental health concerns such as stress and burnout. It also maintains appropriate professional boundaries and ensures compliance with medical practice guidelines.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Doctors should have their own general practitioner to maintain objectivity in their healthcare and avoid self-diagnosis.","Self-prescribing medication is inappropriate and potentially dangerous for healthcare professionals.","Regular preventive care, including immunisations and mental health support, is essential for medical practitioners."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65224"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18877"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65224","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65224"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-16T11:43:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-16T11:46:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11610"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79928"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{